@page "/wiki/poltergeist"

<div class="wiki-container">
	<img src="/Images/GhostIcons/poltergeist.webp" />
	<div class="wiki-text">
		<h1 class="header-text wiki-header">
			Poltergeist
		</h1>
		<hr />
		<div class="text-section grid-split">
			<span class="section-header">Hunting Threshold:</span>
			<div class="sanity-container">
				<img src="/Images/SanityIcons/MediumSanity.png" />
				<div class="threshold-text">50%</div>
			</div>
		</div>
		<hr />
		<div class="text-section">
			<span class="section-header">Evidences</span>
			<div class="grid-split">
				<div class="sanity-container">
					<img src="/Images/Items/Tier1/box.webp" />
					<div class="evidence-text box-text">Spirit Box</div>
				</div>
				<div class="sanity-container">
					<img src="/Images/Items/Tier1/uv.webp" />
					<div class="evidence-text uv-text">UV</div>
				</div>
				<div class="sanity-container">
					<img src="/Images/Items/Tier1/book.webp" />
					<div class="evidence-text book-text">Writing</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
		<hr />
		<div class="text-section">
			<div class="section-header">Abilities<br /></div>
			<div class="wiki-info">
				Poltergeists can throw items with much more force outside and during a hunt.
				<br /><br />
				The Poltergeist can throw multiple items at once (= polter boom or polter explosion), reducing each nearby player's sanity by 2% per item.
				To lose that sanity, the player must be in line-of-sight with the ability's spawn location.
				<br />Thrown items will emit an EMF level 3 and the ability an EMF level 2.
			</div>
			<br />
			<div class="section-header">Hunt</div>
			<div class="wiki-info">
				During a hunt, the Poltergeist will always throw an item every 0.5 seconds.
				<br />The items can be thrown with much more force than usual.
			</div>
			<br />
		</div>
	</div>
</div>